==English==

===Etymology===
from [[Cologne]], the name of the city in Germany

===Noun===
'''cologne'''; plural '''[[colognes]]'''
# A type of [[scented]] or [[perfumed]] water named after the city of Cologne.  Also called ''[[eau de Cologne]]'' or ''[[Kölnisch Wasser]]''.

====Synonyms====
*[[eau de Cologne]] 
*[[Kölnisch Wasser]]

